window.__SCRIBE_DOC_SEARCH__ = [{"page":"index.html","title":"Overview","section":"Get oriented","excerpt":"A practical map of the writing workspace, its current capabilities, and the fastest route into the codebase.","content":"ScribeAI developer documentation This directory describes the application as it works now. It is intended to get a developer from a fresh checkout to making safe changes without first reverse-engineering the UI, editor, and suggestion state machine. What this application is ScribeAI is an Electron writing workspace with a React renderer. The current implementation combines: - a BlockNote rich-text editor; - persistent live and development-injected writing-partner feeds; - an inbox for reading, dismissing, pinning, and previewing suggestions; - desktop workspace cards for keeping references over the editor; - responsive navigation and writing-partner panels; - SQLite document, source, suggestion, transcript, and agent-memory persistence; - a background Pi agent with user-configured inference providers. Electron owns SQLite and Pi in utility processes, imports text, Markdown, JSON, PDF, and DOCX sources, and restores the workspace after restart. Development uses the same runtime with Vite renderer HMR and a dedicated mock-suggestion window. Routing and most document-management controls remain presentation-only. Fastest route into the codebase 1. Follow Getting started and run the app"},{"page":"index.html#what-this-application-is","title":"What this application is","section":"Overview","excerpt":"ScribeAI is an Electron writing workspace with a React renderer. The current implementation combines: - a BlockNote rich-text editor; - persistent live and development-injected writing-partner feeds; - an inbox for readi","content":"What this application is ScribeAI is an Electron writing workspace with a React renderer. The current implementation combines: - a BlockNote rich-text editor; - persistent live and development-injected writing-partner feeds; - an inbox for reading, dismissing, pinning, and previewing suggestions;"},{"page":"index.html#fastest-route-into-the-codebase","title":"Fastest route into the codebase","section":"Overview","excerpt":"1. Follow Getting started and run the app and checks. 2. Read Architecture for state ownership and module boundaries. 3. Read Editor and suggestion system before changing feed, preview, pin, or inbox behavior. 4. Use UI ","content":"Fastest route into the codebase 1. Follow Getting started and run the app and checks. 2. Read Architecture for state ownership and module boundaries. 3. Read Editor and suggestion system before changing feed, preview, pin, or inbox behavior. 4. Use UI and accessibility for responsive layout, resizing, styling, and keyboard behavior."},{"page":"index.html#current-user-visible-behavior","title":"Current user-visible behavior","section":"Overview","excerpt":"","content":"Current user-visible behavior "},{"page":"index.html#repository-map","title":"Repository map","section":"Overview","excerpt":". ├── docs/ Developer documentation ├── desktop/ Electron main, preload, storage, Pi, and build entries ├── src/ │ ├── App.tsx Composition root and cross-feature orchestration │ ├── main.tsx React renderer entry point │ ","content":"Repository map . ├── docs/ Developer documentation ├── desktop/ Electron main, preload, storage, Pi, and build entries ├── src/ │ ├── App.tsx Composition root and cross-feature orchestration │ ├── main.tsx React renderer entry point │ ├── index.css Tailwind theme, layout rules, and editor overrides"},{"page":"index.html#terms-used-in-the-code","title":"Terms used in the code","section":"Overview","excerpt":"- Suggestion feed : the subscription interface that emits suggestion and agent-status events. - Inbox entry : a live suggestion tracked by the reducer, including viewed, stale, and withdrawn flags. - Pinned entry : a dee","content":"Terms used in the code - Suggestion feed : the subscription interface that emits suggestion and agent-status events. - Inbox entry : a live suggestion tracked by the reducer, including viewed, stale, and withdrawn flags. - Pinned entry : a deep-copied, stable suggestion snapshot removed from the live inbox queue."},{"page":"index.html#important-implementation-constraints","title":"Important implementation constraints","section":"Overview","excerpt":"- App.tsx is the renderer composition root. It connects the required Electron bridge, hydration, autosave, feed, previews, panel state, and workspace pins. - inboxReducer is the source of truth for suggestion lifecycle r","content":"Important implementation constraints - App.tsx is the renderer composition root. It connects the required Electron bridge, hydration, autosave, feed, previews, panel state, and workspace pins. - inboxReducer is the source of truth for suggestion lifecycle rules. UI components dispatch intent; they should not recreate those rules locally."},{"page":"getting-started.html","title":"Getting started","section":"Get oriented","excerpt":"Install, run, inspect, and troubleshoot the project from a clean checkout.","content":"Getting started Prerequisites - Node.js =22.19.0. Pi agent-core sets the effective project minimum. - npm, using the committed package-lock.json. No database daemon is required. Electron creates its SQLite database in the platform application-data directory. An API key or local inference endpoint is only required when enabling the Pi agent. Install and run From the repository root: Vite builds the Electron main, preload, storage, and agent entries, starts its renderer development server, and launches Electron. Renderer changes use HMR; main, storage, or agent changes restart Electron; preload changes reload the renderer. Development intentionally uses the same Electron userData directory as a built or installed ScribeAI application. Edits, imported sources, settings, and mock suggestions therefore affect the same persisted workspace. Do not run development and an installed build concurrently against that profile. Use npm ci, rather than npm install, for a clean checkout or CI job so dependency versions remain aligned with the lockfile. To build and launch the persistent desktop application: This command always builds the renderer and Electron processes before launching. The product"},{"page":"getting-started.html#prerequisites","title":"Prerequisites","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"- Node.js =22.19.0. Pi agent-core sets the effective project minimum. - npm, using the committed package-lock.json. No database daemon is required. Electron creates its SQLite database in the platform application-data di","content":"Prerequisites - Node.js =22.19.0. Pi agent-core sets the effective project minimum. - npm, using the committed package-lock.json. No database daemon is required. Electron creates its SQLite database in the platform application-data directory. An API key or local inference endpoint is only required when enabling the Pi agent."},{"page":"getting-started.html#install-and-run","title":"Install and run","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"From the repository root: npm ci npm run dev Vite builds the Electron main, preload, storage, and agent entries, starts its renderer development server, and launches Electron. Renderer changes use HMR; main, storage, or ","content":"Install and run From the repository root: npm ci npm run dev Vite builds the Electron main, preload, storage, and agent entries, starts its renderer development server, and launches Electron. Renderer changes use HMR; main, storage, or agent changes restart Electron; preload changes reload the renderer."},{"page":"getting-started.html#what-to-expect-after-startup","title":"What to expect after startup","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Electron opens the persisted writing workspace. To inject deterministic suggestions without invoking a model: 1. Choose Development → Mock suggestions , or press CmdOrCtrl+Shift+M. 2. Complete one of the six suggestion f","content":"What to expect after startup Electron opens the persisted writing workspace. To inject deterministic suggestions without invoking a model: 1. Choose Development → Mock suggestions , or press CmdOrCtrl+Shift+M. 2. Complete one of the six suggestion forms in the dedicated development window."},{"page":"getting-started.html#developer-commands","title":"Developer commands","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"A normal pre-handoff check is: npm run lint npm test npm run build See Testing and quality for the current automated coverage and manual checks. The production build currently completes with Vite's warning that some mini","content":"Developer commands A normal pre-handoff check is: npm run lint npm test npm run build See Testing and quality for the current automated coverage and manual checks. The production build currently completes with Vite's warning that some minified chunks exceed 500 kB. The main application bundle and parts of Mermaid are the principal contributors. This is a warning, not a failed build; treat a new error separately. The performance watch points in the Extension guide describe the relevant boundaries."},{"page":"getting-started.html#runtime-configuration","title":"Runtime configuration","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"The global agent model is configured in agent.yaml under Electron's userData directory. The file is created on first launch from any legacy SQLite provider settings. Edit it while the app is closed, then restart: version","content":"Runtime configuration The global agent model is configured in agent.yaml under Electron's userData directory. The file is created on first launch from any legacy SQLite provider settings. Edit it while the app is closed, then restart: version: 1 enabled: true provider:"},{"page":"getting-started.html#renderer-preferences","title":"Renderer preferences","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"The app stores two optional values: Invalid or unavailable values are ignored. Double-clicking a resize separator removes its key and restores the CSS default. If browser storage is blocked, resizing still works for the ","content":"Renderer preferences The app stores two optional values: Invalid or unavailable values are ignored. Double-clicking a resize separator removes its key and restores the CSS default. If browser storage is blocked, resizing still works for the current session. These values remain renderer-local in both runtimes. Electron workspace data lives in scribe.sqlite3 under Electron's userData directory."},{"page":"getting-started.html#first-pass-manual-tour","title":"First-pass manual tour","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"At a viewport at least 80rem wide: 1. Inject one suggestion of each kind from Development → Mock suggestions . 2. Open a text suggestion, preview it, edit the purple preview block, then cancel it. 3. Preview again and ac","content":"First-pass manual tour At a viewport at least 80rem wide: 1. Inject one suggestion of each kind from Development → Mock suggestions . 2. Open a text suggestion, preview it, edit the purple preview block, then cancel it. 3. Preview again and accept it; it becomes a normal paragraph and the suggestion disappears."},{"page":"getting-started.html#common-problems","title":"Common problems","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"","content":"Common problems "},{"page":"getting-started.html#vite-refuses-to-start","title":"Vite refuses to start","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Check node --version. Vite 8 does not support early Node 20 releases; use Node 20.19 or newer, or Node 22.12 or newer.","content":"Vite refuses to start Check node --version. Vite 8 does not support early Node 20 releases; use Node 20.19 or newer, or Node 22.12 or newer."},{"page":"getting-started.html#electron-opens-a-blank-window","title":"Electron opens a blank window","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Inspect dist/index.html. Built script, stylesheet, module-preload, and lazy-chunk URLs must be relative to the file, such as ./assets/index-….js. vite.config.ts sets base: \"./\" for this reason. Root-relative /assets/... ","content":"Electron opens a blank window Inspect dist/index.html. Built script, stylesheet, module-preload, and lazy-chunk URLs must be relative to the file, such as ./assets/index-….js. vite.config.ts sets base: \"./\" for this reason. Root-relative /assets/... references resolve from the filesystem root under Electron and fail with ERR FILE NOT FOUND."},{"page":"getting-started.html#electron-starts-but-no-window-appears","title":"Electron starts but no window appears","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Run Electron with logging enabled and inspect Desktop startup failed plus utility-process stderr. Main waits for both storage and agent readiness before creating the window. Keep the ES-module entry free of a top-level a","content":"Electron starts but no window appears Run Electron with logging enabled and inspect Desktop startup failed plus utility-process stderr. Main waits for both storage and agent readiness before creating the window. Keep the ES-module entry free of a top-level await app.whenReady(); startup must be attached with app.whenReady().then(start) so module evaluation can complete."},{"page":"getting-started.html#fonts-look-different","title":"Fonts look different","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"index.html loads Inter and Literata from Google Fonts. If the network request is blocked, the UI falls back to system sans-serif and Georgia-style serif fonts. Functionality is unaffected.","content":"Fonts look different index.html loads Inter and Literata from Google Fonts. If the network request is blocked, the UI falls back to system sans-serif and Georgia-style serif fonts. Functionality is unaffected."},{"page":"getting-started.html#a-mind-map-says-diagram-unavailable","title":"A mind map says “Diagram unavailable”","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Mermaid is loaded lazily only when a mind-map visual renders. Invalid Mermaid source or a failed module render activates the accessible text fallback. Inspect MermaidDiagram.tsx and the mermaidSource on the suggestion.","content":"A mind map says “Diagram unavailable” Mermaid is loaded lazily only when a mind-map visual renders. Invalid Mermaid source or a failed module render activates the accessible text fallback. Inspect MermaidDiagram.tsx and the mermaidSource on the suggestion."},{"page":"getting-started.html#a-workspace-pin-is-missing","title":"A workspace pin is missing","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Workspace cards render only at the desktop xl breakpoint (80rem and above). A card also remains hidden for one animation frame while its initial geometry is calculated. It must first be pinned in the writing partner befo","content":"A workspace pin is missing Workspace cards render only at the desktop xl breakpoint (80rem and above). A card also remains hidden for one animation frame while its initial geometry is calculated. It must first be pinned in the writing partner before “Place on workspace” is available."},{"page":"getting-started.html#suggestion-behavior-seems-duplicated-in-development","title":"Suggestion behavior seems duplicated in development","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Check that a new feed is not being created on every render. App.tsx memoizes it. Also ensure every SuggestionFeed.subscribe implementation fully cleans up when the last subscriber leaves; React StrictMode will exercise t","content":"Suggestion behavior seems duplicated in development Check that a new feed is not being created on every render. App.tsx memoizes it. Also ensure every SuggestionFeed.subscribe implementation fully cleans up when the last subscriber leaves; React StrictMode will exercise that path."},{"page":"getting-started.html#a-manually-sent-suggestion-does-not-appear","title":"A manually sent suggestion does not appear","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Confirm the controller was opened from the Electron Development menu rather than by visiting the Vite URL in a browser. Check the controller error message and main-process logs; development injection is rejected outside ","content":"A manually sent suggestion does not appear Confirm the controller was opened from the Electron Development menu rather than by visiting the Vite URL in a browser. Check the controller error message and main-process logs; development injection is rejected outside the Electron development runtime."},{"page":"architecture.html","title":"Architecture","section":"Get oriented","excerpt":"Understand browser and Electron boundaries, state ownership, data direction, and module responsibilities.","content":"Architecture System boundary The React renderer has one application composition: Electron supplies a required preload bridge, main-process orchestration, a SQLite utility process, and a Pi utility process. Vite serves that renderer inside Electron during development and builds it for file:// loading in production. There is still no routing library. The SuggestionFeed remains transport-neutral, while its only application adapter maps committed Electron events. Desktop queries and commands use the typed DesktopBridge contract. Development injection is a separately gated bridge and enters the same persisted storage/event path. Composition root App.tsx creates and connects long-lived objects: 1. useCreateBlockNote creates the editor from writingSchema and seeded content. 2. createDesktopSuggestionFeed creates the Electron event adapter and is memoized for the component lifetime. 3. useSuggestionInbox subscribes to the feed and owns the suggestion lifecycle reducer. 4. App creates editor preview blocks, translates preview resolution events back into inbox actions, and controls responsive panels. Keeping feed creation stable is important. Recreating it during a render would resubscribe t"},{"page":"architecture.html#system-boundary","title":"System boundary","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"The React renderer has one application composition: Electron supplies a required preload bridge, main-process orchestration, a SQLite utility process, and a Pi utility process. Vite serves that renderer inside Electron d","content":"System boundary The React renderer has one application composition: Electron supplies a required preload bridge, main-process orchestration, a SQLite utility process, and a Pi utility process. Vite serves that renderer inside Electron during development and builds it for file:// loading in production. There is still no routing library."},{"page":"architecture.html#composition-root","title":"Composition root","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"App.tsx creates and connects long-lived objects: 1. useCreateBlockNote creates the editor from writingSchema and seeded content. 2. createDesktopSuggestionFeed creates the Electron event adapter and is memoized for the c","content":"Composition root App.tsx creates and connects long-lived objects: 1. useCreateBlockNote creates the editor from writingSchema and seeded content. 2. createDesktopSuggestionFeed creates the Electron event adapter and is memoized for the component lifetime. 3. useSuggestionInbox subscribes to the feed and owns the suggestion lifecycle reducer."},{"page":"architecture.html#state-ownership","title":"State ownership","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"There is intentionally one owner for each lifecycle. Components such as SuggestionDock, WorkspacePins, and DocumentHeader receive values and callbacks; they do not own duplicate application state.","content":"State ownership There is intentionally one owner for each lifecycle. Components such as SuggestionDock, WorkspacePins, and DocumentHeader receive values and callbacks; they do not own duplicate application state."},{"page":"architecture.html#module-boundaries","title":"Module boundaries","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"","content":"Module boundaries "},{"page":"architecture.html#src-editor","title":"src/editor","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- schema.tsx extends BlockNote with the suggestionPreview block and implements accept/cancel behavior. - previewEvents.ts is a small in-process event bridge from the custom block renderer back to App. The editor layer kn","content":"src/editor - schema.tsx extends BlockNote with the suggestionPreview block and implements accept/cancel behavior. - previewEvents.ts is a small in-process event bridge from the custom block renderer back to App. The editor layer knows suggestion IDs, but it does not import or mutate inbox state."},{"page":"architecture.html#src-suggestions","title":"src/suggestions","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- types.ts defines suggestion data and the feed interface. - validation.ts validates suggestion payloads at runtime before development IPC reaches storage. - inbox.ts implements all suggestion, pin, preview, and workspac","content":"src/suggestions - types.ts defines suggestion data and the feed interface. - validation.ts validates suggestion payloads at runtime before development IPC reaches storage. - inbox.ts implements all suggestion, pin, preview, and workspace transitions. - workspacePinLayout.ts supplies type-specific initial card sizes."},{"page":"architecture.html#src-dev-mocksuggestions","title":"src/dev/mockSuggestions","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"This temporary directory owns the Electron-only controller view and payload builder. Main and preload expose its injection bridge only during Vite development; storage persists accepted mock suggestions exactly like agen","content":"src/dev/mockSuggestions This temporary directory owns the Electron-only controller view and payload builder. Main and preload expose its injection bridge only during Vite development; storage persists accepted mock suggestions exactly like agent-created suggestions."},{"page":"architecture.html#desktop-and-src-desktop","title":"desktop and src/desktop","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- desktop/main.ts owns Electron lifecycle, renderer IPC, utility processes, and the 10-second scheduler. - desktop/storage.ts owns schema creation, SQLite queries, source extraction, committed events, and agent persisten","content":"desktop and src/desktop - desktop/main.ts owns Electron lifecycle, renderer IPC, utility processes, and the 10-second scheduler. - desktop/storage.ts owns schema creation, SQLite queries, source extraction, committed events, and agent persistence. - desktop/agent.ts embeds Pi agent-core, defines domain tools, records transcripts, and coalesces observations."},{"page":"architecture.html#src-components","title":"src/components","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- EditorWorkspace.tsx joins the document header and editor surface. - DocumentEditor.tsx renders BlockNote and calculates initial workspace-card placement. - SuggestionDock.tsx renders the inbox, pinned section, detail v","content":"src/components - EditorWorkspace.tsx joins the document header and editor surface. - DocumentEditor.tsx renders BlockNote and calculates initial workspace-card placement. - SuggestionDock.tsx renders the inbox, pinned section, detail view, and errors. - WorkspacePins.tsx renders desktop cards and handles bounded pointer/keyboard geometry."},{"page":"architecture.html#renderer-bootstrap-sequence","title":"Renderer bootstrap sequence","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"The renderer refuses to construct App without the Electron bridge. The complete process startup is documented separately in Desktop persistence and Pi runtime. sequenceDiagram participant Main as main.tsx participant App","content":"Renderer bootstrap sequence The renderer refuses to construct App without the Electron bridge. The complete process startup is documented separately in Desktop persistence and Pi runtime. sequenceDiagram participant Main as main.tsx participant App participant Editor as BlockNote"},{"page":"architecture.html#data-direction-and-dependency-rules","title":"Data direction and dependency rules","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"The intended dependency direction is: types/contracts ↑ editor utilities suggestion implementations ↑ ↑ components ← props/callbacks → App composition root Practical rules: - Domain contracts belong in suggestions/types.","content":"Data direction and dependency rules The intended dependency direction is: types/contracts ↑ editor utilities suggestion implementations ↑ ↑ components ← props/callbacks → App composition root Practical rules: - Domain contracts belong in suggestions/types.ts, not in UI components."},{"page":"architecture.html#styling-architecture","title":"Styling architecture","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"Tailwind CSS 4 is loaded through the Vite plugin and @import \"tailwindcss\" in index.css. Most component styling is inline utility classes. The global stylesheet is reserved for: - theme tokens and brand colors; - base fo","content":"Styling architecture Tailwind CSS 4 is loaded through the Vite plugin and @import \"tailwindcss\" in index.css. Most component styling is inline utility classes. The global stylesheet is reserved for: - theme tokens and brand colors; - base focus and typography rules;"},{"page":"architecture.html#build-and-runtime-assumptions","title":"Build and runtime assumptions","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- TypeScript is strict and emits no files during type-checking. - Vite targets a browser application; there is no server-side rendering guard around browser globals. - Vite's base is ./ because the production renderer is","content":"Build and runtime assumptions - TypeScript is strict and emits no files during type-checking. - Vite targets a browser application; there is no server-side rendering guard around browser globals. - Vite's base is ./ because the production renderer is loaded from file://; changing it back to / breaks all built renderer assets in Electron."},{"page":"architecture.html#architectural-invariants","title":"Architectural invariants","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"Changes should preserve these unless the design is deliberately revised and documented: 1. Only one editable suggestion preview can exist at a time. 2. Preview content is user-owned once inserted; feed updates never over","content":"Architectural invariants Changes should preserve these unless the design is deliberately revised and documented: 1. Only one editable suggestion preview can exist at a time. 2. Preview content is user-owned once inserted; feed updates never overwrite it. 3. Pinned suggestions are frozen snapshots and ignore later feed updates or retractions."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html","title":"Desktop & Pi","section":"Build internals","excerpt":"Trace Electron processes, SQLite persistence, source import, events, and background Pi observations.","content":"Desktop persistence and Pi runtime Process topology The packaged application has four cooperating runtimes: 1. The React renderer owns BlockNote and presentation state. 2. Electron main owns application lifecycle, IPC routing, file-backed model configuration, and the observation timer. 3. The storage utility process is the only SQLite owner. 4. The agent utility process runs @earendil-works/pi-agent-core with application-domain tools. The preload exposes named methods from DesktopBridge. The renderer never imports Electron, SQLite, or Pi packages. Startup and renderer loading The Electron entry is an ES module. It registers startup with app.whenReady().then(start) rather than using a top-level await app.whenReady(): Electron does not emit ready until the entry module has finished evaluating, so awaiting that event during module evaluation deadlocks startup. start forks both utility processes and waits for an explicit ready message from each before it registers IPC handlers or creates a window. If either child exits first, its readiness promise rejects and main logs Desktop startup failed before quitting instead of leaving a hidden process running indefinitely. In a production launc"},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#process-topology","title":"Process topology","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"The packaged application has four cooperating runtimes: 1. The React renderer owns BlockNote and presentation state. 2. Electron main owns application lifecycle, IPC routing, file-backed model configuration, and the obse","content":"Process topology The packaged application has four cooperating runtimes: 1. The React renderer owns BlockNote and presentation state. 2. Electron main owns application lifecycle, IPC routing, file-backed model configuration, and the observation timer. 3. The storage utility process is the only SQLite owner."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#startup-and-renderer-loading","title":"Startup and renderer loading","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"The Electron entry is an ES module. It registers startup with app.whenReady().then(start) rather than using a top-level await app.whenReady(): Electron does not emit ready until the entry module has finished evaluating, ","content":"Startup and renderer loading The Electron entry is an ES module. It registers startup with app.whenReady().then(start) rather than using a top-level await app.whenReady(): Electron does not emit ready until the entry module has finished evaluating, so awaiting that event during module evaluation deadlocks startup."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#development-suggestion-window","title":"Development suggestion window","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"Vite development adds a Development → Mock suggestions menu command. It opens one dedicated Electron window at /mock-suggestions. A command-line argument enables a separate preload bridge in development windows, and main","content":"Development suggestion window Vite development adds a Development → Mock suggestions menu command. It opens one dedicated Electron window at /mock-suggestions. A command-line argument enables a separate preload bridge in development windows, and main registers the corresponding IPC handler only while VITE DEV SERVER URL is present. Valid suggestions are committed by storage and broadcast like agent-created suggestions. The menu, bridge, handler, and controller chunk are unavailable in production."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#persistence-model","title":"Persistence model","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"The database is scribe.sqlite3 under Electron's userData directory. Startup creates a default project and document and enables SQLite WAL mode. Schema creation is idempotent. The current implementation persists: - the la","content":"Persistence model The database is scribe.sqlite3 under Electron's userData directory. Startup creates a default project and document and enables SQLite WAL mode. Schema creation is idempotent. The current implementation persists: - the latest accepted BlockNote block snapshot and monotonic document/project revisions;"},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#editor-and-event-flow","title":"Editor and event flow","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"On mount, App hydrates a WorkspaceSnapshot, replaces seeded BlockNote content, restores suggestions, and enables autosave. Editor changes are debounced for 650 ms. Suggestion reducer changes save a durable projection. St","content":"Editor and event flow On mount, App hydrates a WorkspaceSnapshot, replaces seeded BlockNote content, restores suggestions, and enables autosave. Editor changes are debounced for 650 ms. Suggestion reducer changes save a durable projection. Storage mutations write canonical data and any desktop event in one transaction. After commit, the storage process forwards outbox events through main to every renderer. The desktop feed converts suggestion and agent runtime events into the existing SuggestionEvent variants."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#source-import","title":"Source import","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"The sidebar's Upload Sources action opens the native file picker. The storage process copies the file into the application-data sources directory and extracts text from: - plain text, Markdown, and JSON with UTF-8 reads;","content":"Source import The sidebar's Upload Sources action opens the native file picker. The storage process copies the file into the application-data sources directory and extracts text from: - plain text, Markdown, and JSON with UTF-8 reads; - DOCX with Mammoth;"},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#agent-lifecycle","title":"Agent lifecycle","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"The scheduler checks every 10 seconds while the app is open. It starts a run only when the project revision differs from the last completed observation. Only one run executes at once; newer observations are coalesced. Ea","content":"Agent lifecycle The scheduler checks every 10 seconds while the app is open. It starts a run only when the project revision differs from the last completed observation. Only one run executes at once; newer observations are coalesced. Each run receives the active project/document IDs and revisions plus the previous document-memory summary. Its tools can list, search, and read project content; list current suggestions; create, update, or retract live suggestions; and save the next memory summary. Suggestion and memory writes fail when the document revision has changed."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#failure-behaviour","title":"Failure behaviour","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"- A utility process that exits before its ready message rejects desktop startup; main logs the error and quits. - Provider or tool errors update the writing-partner error state and mark the run failed. - Runs time out af","content":"Failure behaviour - A utility process that exits before its ready message rejects desktop startup; main logs the error and quits. - Provider or tool errors update the writing-partner error state and mark the run failed. - Runs time out after two minutes. - Storage errors reject the originating IPC or agent tool call."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#build-and-packaging","title":"Build and packaging","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"vite-plugin-electron integrates renderer, main, preload, storage, and agent builds while preserving the dist/ and dist-electron/ package layout. npm run build type-checks both TypeScript projects before the integrated pr","content":"Build and packaging vite-plugin-electron integrates renderer, main, preload, storage, and agent builds while preserving the dist/ and dist-electron/ package layout. npm run build type-checks both TypeScript projects before the integrated production build. npm run desktop performs that build before launching Electron. npm run package produces an unpacked electron-builder application, while npm run dist produces the configured platform packages. Generated dist-electron/ and release/ directories are not source and remain ignored by Git."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html","title":"Editor & suggestions","section":"Build internals","excerpt":"Trace agent context, feed events, inbox transitions, editable previews, and workspace pins end to end.","content":"Editor and suggestion system This is the core interaction model: the Electron feed emits committed events, the inbox reducer turns those events and user actions into state, and text suggestions can temporarily enter the document as editable previews. Domain model The shared contracts are in src/suggestions/types.ts. Suggestion kinds Kind Type Extra data Can preview into document? Visual treatment --- --- --- --- --- snippet TextSuggestion insertText Yes Text detail fact TextSuggestion insertText Yes Text detail term TextSuggestion insertText Yes Text detail outline StructureSuggestion recursive nodes No Nested structure cards layout StructureSuggestion recursive nodes No Nested structure cards mindMap MindMapSuggestion Mermaid source and accessible description No Lazy-rendered Mermaid diagram Every suggestion also carries: - id: identity for updates, retractions, selection, and actions; - dedupeKey: session-level duplicate prevention for additions; - title, summary, and body: progressively more detailed presentation text; - sourceLabels: display-only attribution labels; - createdAt: ordering and queue-eviction input. An update uses id to replace an existing live item. An addition u"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#domain-model","title":"Domain model","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"The shared contracts are in src/suggestions/types.ts.","content":"Domain model The shared contracts are in src/suggestions/types.ts."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#suggestion-kinds","title":"Suggestion kinds","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"Every suggestion also carries: - id: identity for updates, retractions, selection, and actions; - dedupeKey: session-level duplicate prevention for additions; - title, summary, and body: progressively more detailed prese","content":"Suggestion kinds Every suggestion also carries: - id: identity for updates, retractions, selection, and actions; - dedupeKey: session-level duplicate prevention for additions; - title, summary, and body: progressively more detailed presentation text; - sourceLabels: display-only attribution labels;"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#feed-contract","title":"Feed contract","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"SuggestionFeed is subscription-only: interface SuggestionFeed { subscribe(listener: (event: SuggestionEvent) = void): () = void; } The event channel supports: The renderer uses createDesktopSuggestionFeed. It receives su","content":"Feed contract SuggestionFeed is subscription-only: interface SuggestionFeed { subscribe(listener: (event: SuggestionEvent) = void): () = void; } The event channel supports: The renderer uses createDesktopSuggestionFeed. It receives suggestion and agent-status events from Electron main. Suggestions are written to the desktop database before an event is forwarded, so reload hydrates the same inbox projection."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#inbox-state-machine","title":"Inbox state machine","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"inboxReducer owns: entries live inbox suggestions pinnedEntries frozen references in the Pins section workspacePins frozen references placed over the editor seenKeys dedupe keys accepted during this page session selected","content":"Inbox state machine inboxReducer owns: entries live inbox suggestions pinnedEntries frozen references in the Pins section workspacePins frozen references placed over the editor seenKeys dedupe keys accepted during this page session selectedId item shown in detail view"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#feed-event-behavior","title":"Feed-event behavior","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"","content":"Feed-event behavior "},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#queue-limit","title":"Queue limit","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"The live queue is limited to 30. Pins and workspace cards do not count. If eviction is necessary: 1. the selected item and active preview are protected; 2. viewed items are evicted before unread items; 3. within that gro","content":"Queue limit The live queue is limited to 30. Pins and workspace cards do not count. If eviction is necessary: 1. the selected item and active preview are protected; 2. viewed items are evicted before unread items; 3. within that group, the oldest createdAt value is evicted first."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#user-action-behavior","title":"User-action behavior","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"- Selecting marks the item viewed and opens detail. - Back clears detail and removes withdrawn entries unless one still owns the active preview. - Dismiss removes an inbox or pinned item and closes its detail view. Dismi","content":"User-action behavior - Selecting marks the item viewed and opens detail. - Back clears detail and removes withdrawn entries unless one still owns the active preview. - Dismiss removes an inbox or pinned item and closes its detail view. Dismiss is disabled while that item has the active preview."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#editable-preview-lifecycle","title":"Editable preview lifecycle","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"Only snippet, fact, and term suggestions expose “Preview in document.” The orchestration is split between App, the custom BlockNote block, and the inbox reducer. sequenceDiagram participant User participant Dock as Sugge","content":"Editable preview lifecycle Only snippet, fact, and term suggestions expose “Preview in document.” The orchestration is split between App, the custom BlockNote block, and the inbox reducer. sequenceDiagram participant User participant Dock as SuggestionDock participant App"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#preview-insertion","title":"Preview insertion","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"App.handlePreview rejects the request when: - another preview is active; - the suggestion is not a text suggestion; - there is no accepted reference block. It finds the most recently selected text block among accepted bl","content":"Preview insertion App.handlePreview rejects the request when: - another preview is active; - the suggestion is not a text suggestion; - there is no accepted reference block. It finds the most recently selected text block among accepted blocks. If that block no longer exists, it falls back to the final accepted top-level block. The preview is inserted immediately after that block with:"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#preview-rendering-and-resolution","title":"Preview rendering and resolution","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"schema.tsx registers suggestionPreview alongside BlockNote's default blocks. Its React renderer owns the buttons: - Accept is disabled if recursive content inspection finds no visible text. - Accept replaces the custom b","content":"Preview rendering and resolution schema.tsx registers suggestionPreview alongside BlockNote's default blocks. Its React renderer owns the buttons: - Accept is disabled if recursive content inspection finds no visible text. - Accept replaces the custom block with a normal paragraph carrying the edited inline content."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#concurrent-feed-changes","title":"Concurrent feed changes","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"The preview is a snapshot. If the feed updates the source suggestion, the detail view reports that the item was refined, but the user's editable block is never rewritten. If the feed retracts it, the detail view reports ","content":"Concurrent feed changes The preview is a snapshot. If the feed updates the source suggestion, the detail view reports that the item was refined, but the user's editable block is never rewritten. If the feed retracts it, the detail view reports withdrawal and the preview remains resolvable. Cancelling a withdrawn preview removes the suggestion; accepting any preview removes it."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#pins-and-workspace-cards","title":"Pins and workspace cards","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"Pins are a separate lifecycle from previews: stateDiagram-v2 [ ] -- Inbox: suggestion.added Inbox -- Pins: Pin Pins -- Inbox: Unpin Pins -- Workspace: Place on workspace (desktop) Workspace -- Pins: Return to Pins Inbox ","content":"Pins and workspace cards Pins are a separate lifecycle from previews: stateDiagram-v2 [ ] -- Inbox: suggestion.added Inbox -- Pins: Pin Pins -- Inbox: Unpin Pins -- Workspace: Place on workspace (desktop) Workspace -- Pins: Return to Pins Inbox -- [ ]: Dismiss / accepted preview / retraction"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#mermaid-rendering","title":"Mermaid rendering","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"Mind maps use MermaidDiagram: - the mermaid package is imported once, lazily; - the singleton is initialized with securityLevel: \"strict\" and startOnLoad: false; - React IDs are sanitized into per-render Mermaid IDs; - t","content":"Mermaid rendering Mind maps use MermaidDiagram: - the mermaid package is imported once, lazily; - the singleton is initialized with securityLevel: \"strict\" and startOnLoad: false; - React IDs are sanitized into per-render Mermaid IDs; - the rendered SVG is injected into a role=\"img\" container with a combined title and accessible description;"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html","title":"UI & accessibility","section":"Build internals","excerpt":"Work confidently with responsive panels, editor layout, keyboard input, focus, and visual conventions.","content":"UI and accessibility Page regions The application has three conceptual regions: 1. project navigation; 2. the document workspace (header and editor); 3. the writing partner. App renders one desktop grid plus two below-desktop drawers. EditorWorkspace keeps the document header and editor together as the center region. Responsive layout The desktop threshold is 80rem (xl in Tailwind's default scale and the explicit media query in index.css). Viewport Navigation Document Writing partner Workspace cards --- --- --- --- --- =96rem Default 280 px Fluid Default 360 px Visible Opening suggestion detail applies a wider default writing-partner width (clamp(30rem, 38vw, 40rem)) in the first desktop range. An inline user-saved width takes precedence. At 96rem and above, the later large-screen default currently wins in the CSS cascade. Desktop panel open state and mobile drawer open state are intentionally separate. Crossing into desktop closes any open drawers. Collapsing a desktop panel does not imply that its mobile drawer is open, and vice versa. Desktop column resizing ColumnResizeHandle renders an accessible vertical separator on each open side column. Limits Column Minimum Absolute maxim"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#page-regions","title":"Page regions","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"The application has three conceptual regions: 1. project navigation; 2. the document workspace (header and editor); 3. the writing partner. App renders one desktop grid plus two below-desktop drawers. EditorWorkspace kee","content":"Page regions The application has three conceptual regions: 1. project navigation; 2. the document workspace (header and editor); 3. the writing partner. App renders one desktop grid plus two below-desktop drawers. EditorWorkspace keeps the document header and editor together as the center region."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#responsive-layout","title":"Responsive layout","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"The desktop threshold is 80rem (xl in Tailwind's default scale and the explicit media query in index.css). Opening suggestion detail applies a wider default writing-partner width (clamp(30rem, 38vw, 40rem)) in the first ","content":"Responsive layout The desktop threshold is 80rem (xl in Tailwind's default scale and the explicit media query in index.css). Opening suggestion detail applies a wider default writing-partner width (clamp(30rem, 38vw, 40rem)) in the first desktop range. An inline user-saved width takes precedence. At 96rem and above, the later large-screen default currently wins in the CSS cascade."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#desktop-column-resizing","title":"Desktop column resizing","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"ColumnResizeHandle renders an accessible vertical separator on each open side column.","content":"Desktop column resizing ColumnResizeHandle renders an accessible vertical separator on each open side column."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#limits","title":"Limits","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"When the viewport changes, saved widths are constrained again. The values are written to localStorage as the user resizes.","content":"Limits When the viewport changes, saved widths are constrained again. The values are written to localStorage as the user resizes."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#input-behavior","title":"Input behavior","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"- Pointer drag resizes in the expected visual direction. - Arrow keys resize by 16 px. - Home moves to the minimum. - End moves to the current dynamic maximum. - Double-click resets to the responsive CSS default and remo","content":"Input behavior - Pointer drag resizes in the expected visual direction. - Arrow keys resize by 16 px. - Home moves to the minimum. - End moves to the current dynamic maximum. - Double-click resets to the responsive CSS default and removes the stored value."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#responsive-drawers","title":"Responsive drawers","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"ResponsiveDrawer provides both side drawers below desktop: - semantic modal dialog with an accessible title; - backdrop click and explicit close button; - Escape-to-close; - initial focus on the close button; - Tab/Shift","content":"Responsive drawers ResponsiveDrawer provides both side drawers below desktop: - semantic modal dialog with an accessible title; - backdrop click and explicit close button; - Escape-to-close; - initial focus on the close button; - Tab/Shift+Tab wrapping inside known focusable elements;"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#header-controls","title":"Header controls","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"DocumentHeader uses separate controls for desktop columns and mobile drawers, each with the correct aria-controls and aria-expanded state. When the writing partner is not visible, its toggle includes the unread count in ","content":"Header controls DocumentHeader uses separate controls for desktop columns and mobile drawers, each with the correct aria-controls and aria-expanded state. When the writing partner is not visible, its toggle includes the unread count in both the visual badge and accessible label. When the desktop partner is already open, the header suppresses its unread badge because the count is visible in the dock."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#editor-surface","title":"Editor surface","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"DocumentEditor is the only vertically scrolling center-region surface. It renders: - a centered BlockNote editor with a maximum content width of 55rem; - an absolute workspace-card layer over the full editor canvas; - ex","content":"Editor surface DocumentEditor is the only vertically scrolling center-region surface. It renders: - a centered BlockNote editor with a maximum content width of 55rem; - an absolute workspace-card layer over the full editor canvas; - extra minimum canvas height when a workspace card extends beyond the document."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#suggestion-dock-interaction","title":"Suggestion dock interaction","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"The writing partner has two mutually exclusive views: - queue view: error, Pins, and live inbox; - detail view: full suggestion, sources, visual content, and actions. Selecting an item marks it viewed and scrolls the doc","content":"Suggestion dock interaction The writing partner has two mutually exclusive views: - queue view: error, Pins, and live inbox; - detail view: full suggestion, sources, visual content, and actions. Selecting an item marks it viewed and scrolls the dock to the top. Unread live and pinned entries contribute to the count. Workspace cards do not."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#workspace-card-input-and-bounds","title":"Workspace card input and bounds","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"Workspace cards are desktop reference surfaces, not editor content. WorkspacePins supports: - pointer drag through the card header; - pointer resize through the bottom-right handle; - raising a card when it is interacted","content":"Workspace card input and bounds Workspace cards are desktop reference surfaces, not editor content. WorkspacePins supports: - pointer drag through the card header; - pointer resize through the bottom-right handle; - raising a card when it is interacted with; - automatic clamping when canvas dimensions change;"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#focus-and-semantics-checklist","title":"Focus and semantics checklist","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"When changing UI behavior, retain these existing properties: - icon-only buttons have explicit labels and decorative icons use aria-hidden; - panel controls expose the controlled element and expanded state; - drawers are","content":"Focus and semantics checklist When changing UI behavior, retain these existing properties: - icon-only buttons have explicit labels and decorative icons use aria-hidden; - panel controls expose the controlled element and expanded state; - drawers are named modal dialogs and restore focus;"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#styling-conventions","title":"Styling conventions","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"Use Tailwind utilities in components for local layout and presentation. Add global CSS only when a selector must target third-party/editor markup, define shared tokens, or coordinate the workspace grid. The brand palette","content":"Styling conventions Use Tailwind utilities in components for local layout and presentation. Add global CSS only when a selector must target third-party/editor markup, define shared tokens, or coordinate the workspace grid. The brand palette is declared as brand-50 through brand-900 in index.css. BlockNote has a parallel set of --bn- variables in the same file. When changing a core color, check both systems as well as hard-coded neutral colors in components."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#static-prototype-surfaces","title":"Static prototype surfaces","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"Do not infer application behavior from every button currently visible. The sidebar navigation, document-management actions, and tabs are static. Source upload is functional: App supplies persisted source data and an Elec","content":"Static prototype surfaces Do not infer application behavior from every button currently visible. The sidebar navigation, document-management actions, and tabs are static. Source upload is functional: App supplies persisted source data and an Electron import callback to Sidebar. When implementing the remaining controls, add an explicit state/data owner and update this documentation; avoid placing navigation or persistence side effects directly inside presentational components."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html","title":"Testing & quality","section":"Ship safely","excerpt":"Know what the automated suite protects, where browser checks are required, and what to run before handoff.","content":"Testing and quality Test stack - Vitest 4 runs the test suite. - jsdom supplies the browser-like environment configured in vite.config.ts. - Testing Library renders React components and queries their accessible output. - @testing-library/user-event drives user-style interactions. - src/test/setup.ts cleans up rendered React trees after every test. Tests are colocated with source files and use .test.ts or .test.tsx. Commands npm run build is also the authoritative type and bundle check. It type-checks the renderer and Electron projects, then runs the integrated Vite build for renderer, main, preload, storage, and agent entries. TypeScript uses strict mode, rejects unused locals and parameters, and disallows fallthrough switch cases. Current automated coverage The suite currently contains 34 tests across eight files. File What it protects --- --- suggestions/inbox.test.ts Dedupe, 30-item eviction, stale/withdrawn previews, frozen pins, workspace transitions, preview resolution, and z-order. dev/mockSuggestions/mockSuggestionDraft.test.ts Common metadata, every kind-specific payload, recursive node JSON, and validation failures. dev/mockSuggestions/MockSuggestionController.test.tsx Dy"},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#test-stack","title":"Test stack","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Vitest 4 runs the test suite. - jsdom supplies the browser-like environment configured in vite.config.ts. - Testing Library renders React components and queries their accessible output. - @testing-library/user-event dr","content":"Test stack - Vitest 4 runs the test suite. - jsdom supplies the browser-like environment configured in vite.config.ts. - Testing Library renders React components and queries their accessible output. - @testing-library/user-event drives user-style interactions."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#commands","title":"Commands","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"npm test npm run test:watch npm run lint npm run build npm run build is also the authoritative type and bundle check. It type-checks the renderer and Electron projects, then runs the integrated Vite build for renderer, m","content":"Commands npm test npm run test:watch npm run lint npm run build npm run build is also the authoritative type and bundle check. It type-checks the renderer and Electron projects, then runs the integrated Vite build for renderer, main, preload, storage, and agent entries. TypeScript uses strict mode, rejects unused locals and parameters, and disallows fallthrough switch cases."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#current-automated-coverage","title":"Current automated coverage","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"The suite currently contains 34 tests across eight files.","content":"Current automated coverage The suite currently contains 34 tests across eight files."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#why-reducer-tests-matter-most","title":"Why reducer tests matter most","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"The inbox reducer contains the application's lifecycle invariants and is pure. Any change to dedupe, updates, retractions, selection, previewing, pins, workspace geometry, queue limits, or unread behavior should begin wi","content":"Why reducer tests matter most The inbox reducer contains the application's lifecycle invariants and is pure. Any change to dedupe, updates, retractions, selection, previewing, pins, workspace geometry, queue limits, or unread behavior should begin with a reducer case. Component tests should then verify that the correct intent is exposed to users."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#development-injection-tests","title":"Development injection tests","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"The controller test injects a callback rather than Electron IPC. Storage tests protect durable development suggestion behavior; manually confirm the development-only preload and main-process gates in Electron.","content":"Development injection tests The controller test injects a callback rather than Electron IPC. Storage tests protect durable development suggestion behavior; manually confirm the development-only preload and main-process gates in Electron."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#geometry-tests","title":"Geometry tests","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"jsdom does not perform layout. Workspace tests mock clientWidth and clientHeight, and pointer-capture methods are stubbed where needed. A passing geometry unit test does not replace Electron renderer testing for actual s","content":"Geometry tests jsdom does not perform layout. Workspace tests mock clientWidth and clientHeight, and pointer-capture methods are stubbed where needed. A passing geometry unit test does not replace Electron renderer testing for actual scroll, resizing, and pointer behavior."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#what-is-not-covered-automatically","title":"What is not covered automatically","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"The current suite does not render the full App or BlockNote editor. It therefore does not directly verify: - preview block insertion, editing, accepting, or cancellation; - panel drag resizing and localStorage restoratio","content":"What is not covered automatically The current suite does not render the full App or BlockNote editor. It therefore does not directly verify: - preview block insertion, editing, accepting, or cancellation; - panel drag resizing and localStorage restoration; - breakpoint transitions and drawer/desktop handoff;"},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#manual-regression-checklist","title":"Manual regression checklist","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"","content":"Manual regression checklist "},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#editor","title":"Editor","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- The seeded document renders and remains editable. - Editing document text does not create suggestions. - Block formatting, selection, slash menu, and normal BlockNote editing still work.","content":"Editor - The seeded document renders and remains editable. - Editing document text does not create suggestions. - Block formatting, selection, slash menu, and normal BlockNote editing still work."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#suggestion-lifecycle","title":"Suggestion lifecycle","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- The inbox remains empty until a controller event is sent. - Each of the six controller kinds appears with its entered content and visual treatment. - The workspace exposes no Generate Ideas, steering, or retry controls","content":"Suggestion lifecycle - The inbox remains empty until a controller event is sent. - Each of the six controller kinds appears with its entered content and visual treatment. - The workspace exposes no Generate Ideas, steering, or retry controls. - Selecting marks an item read; Back returns to the correct queue."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#preview-lifecycle","title":"Preview lifecycle","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Only text kinds offer Preview. - The preview appears after the last active accepted block and receives focus. - Only one preview can be active. - The preview is editable; empty content disables Accept. - Cancel removes","content":"Preview lifecycle - Only text kinds offer Preview. - The preview appears after the last active accepted block and receives focus. - Only one preview can be active. - The preview is editable; empty content disables Accept. - Cancel removes the block and keeps a normal source suggestion."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#desktop-layout-80rem","title":"Desktop layout ( =80rem)","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Both side columns can collapse independently. - Pointer and keyboard resizing respect the editor's minimum space. - Reload restores sizes; double-click resets them. - A pinned detail can be placed on the workspace. - C","content":"Desktop layout ( =80rem) - Both side columns can collapse independently. - Pointer and keyboard resizing respect the editor's minimum space. - Reload restores sizes; double-click resets them. - A pinned detail can be placed on the workspace. - Cards move, resize, stack, clamp, scroll internally, and return to Pins."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#below-desktop-80rem","title":"Below desktop (<80rem)","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Navigation and writing partner open as the correct side drawers. - Escape, backdrop, and close button dismiss a drawer. - Focus enters the drawer, wraps, and returns to the trigger. - Workspace placement is unavailable","content":"Below desktop (<80rem) - Navigation and writing partner open as the correct side drawers. - Escape, backdrop, and close button dismiss a drawer. - Focus enters the drawer, wraps, and returns to the trigger. - Workspace placement is unavailable and no workspace card is shown."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#accessibility","title":"Accessibility","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Complete core flows with keyboard only. - Inspect button/dialog/region names with browser accessibility tools. - Confirm visible focus on all interactive elements. - Confirm unread counts and errors are announced as te","content":"Accessibility - Complete core flows with keyboard only. - Inspect button/dialog/region names with browser accessibility tools. - Confirm visible focus on all interactive elements. - Confirm unread counts and errors are announced as text, not color alone. - Force invalid Mermaid source and confirm the description remains available."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#electron-runtime","title":"Electron runtime","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Run npm run dev and confirm Electron launches without manually opening the Vite URL. - Change renderer code and confirm HMR; change main/storage/agent code and confirm Electron restarts; change preload and confirm the ","content":"Electron runtime - Run npm run dev and confirm Electron launches without manually opening the Vite URL. - Change renderer code and confirm HMR; change main/storage/agent code and confirm Electron restarts; change preload and confirm the renderer reloads. - Open Development → Mock suggestions twice and confirm one controller window is focused rather than duplicated."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#adding-tests","title":"Adding tests","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"Match the test boundary to the behavior: - pure state transition: add to inbox.test.ts; - feed adapter lifecycle: test through SuggestionFeed events with fake time or a controlled transport; - component semantics/callbac","content":"Adding tests Match the test boundary to the behavior: - pure state transition: add to inbox.test.ts; - feed adapter lifecycle: test through SuggestionFeed events with fake time or a controlled transport; - component semantics/callback: render the component with explicit props and query by accessible role/name;"},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#pre-handoff-standard","title":"Pre-handoff standard","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"Before handing off a change: 1. run lint; 2. run all unit/component tests; 3. run the production build; 4. manually exercise each changed flow at the relevant breakpoints; 5. update /docs if a contract, invariant, comman","content":"Pre-handoff standard Before handing off a change: 1. run lint; 2. run all unit/component tests; 3. run the production build; 4. manually exercise each changed flow at the relevant breakpoints; 5. update /docs if a contract, invariant, command, breakpoint, persistence rule, or static/functional boundary changed."},{"page":"extension-guide.html","title":"Extension guide","section":"Ship safely","excerpt":"Use the existing seams to add a real agent, persistence, suggestion kinds, editor blocks, and application actions.","content":"Extension guide This guide identifies the existing seams for likely next steps in the Electron runtime. Evolve the writing-partner transport Keep transport details behind the existing SuggestionFeed contract. The Electron adapter receives committed events from the storage and Pi processes; the development controller injects through that same persisted path. A production adapter must define: - how it starts and stops when subscribers come and go; - how server messages map to every SuggestionEvent variant; - stable id and dedupeKey rules; - reconnection and replay semantics; - ordering of status, suggestion, and error events; - cleanup under React StrictMode. Choose or introduce adapters at the construction boundary in App.tsx. Preserve stable construction with useMemo, or move service creation above React if it is intentionally process-wide. Do not call an HTTP or model SDK directly from SuggestionDock. That would couple view lifecycle to transport lifecycle, make replay/dedupe inconsistent, and bypass reducer tests. Introduce context for a real service The current application does not publish editor or artifact context to the feed. Before introducing a network payload, decide and d"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#evolve-the-writing-partner-transport","title":"Evolve the writing-partner transport","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Keep transport details behind the existing SuggestionFeed contract. The Electron adapter receives committed events from the storage and Pi processes; the development controller injects through that same persisted path. A","content":"Evolve the writing-partner transport Keep transport details behind the existing SuggestionFeed contract. The Electron adapter receives committed events from the storage and Pi processes; the development controller injects through that same persisted path. A production adapter must define:"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#introduce-context-for-a-real-service","title":"Introduce context for a real service","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The current application does not publish editor or artifact context to the feed. Before introducing a network payload, decide and document: - whether block IDs are stable across saved sessions; - whether formatting, hier","content":"Introduce context for a real service The current application does not publish editor or artifact context to the feed. Before introducing a network payload, decide and document: - whether block IDs are stable across saved sessions; - whether formatting, hierarchy, current selection, title, and metadata are required;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#extend-persistence","title":"Extend persistence","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The desktop runtime persists through its storage process and SQLite database. Keep the existing separation between document data, suggestion projection, sources, agent records, and the separately validated agent.yaml mod","content":"Extend persistence The desktop runtime persists through its storage process and SQLite database. Keep the existing separation between document data, suggestion projection, sources, agent records, and the separately validated agent.yaml model configuration rather than replacing it with one opaque React-state blob."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#document-data","title":"Document data","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Document saves contain BlockNote's serializable document model and metadata. Accepted content is autosaved after a short debounce, and startup hydration replaces the initial renderer seed. Preserve schema-version handlin","content":"Document data Document saves contain BlockNote's serializable document model and metadata. Accepted content is autosaved after a short debounce, and startup hydration replaces the initial renderer seed. Preserve schema-version handling as the custom block set evolves."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#suggestion-data","title":"Suggestion data","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The live inbox, pins, workspace cards, dedupe keys, and geometry are stored as a document-scoped projection. Changes to dedupe retention should be made deliberately because a dismissed item currently cannot be re-added w","content":"Suggestion data The live inbox, pins, workspace cards, dedupe keys, and geometry are stored as a document-scoped projection. Changes to dedupe retention should be made deliberately because a dismissed item currently cannot be re-added with the same key. Pinned entries are user-owned frozen snapshots. Preserve that distinction if live suggestions are server-backed: server updates should not mutate a saved pin."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#workspace-preferences","title":"Workspace preferences","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Column widths remain renderer-local preferences. Workspace-card geometry is stored per document and restored through the same clamp path because available canvas dimensions change. Add new durable data through the storag","content":"Workspace preferences Column widths remain renderer-local preferences. Workspace-card geometry is stored per document and restored through the same clamp path because available canvas dimensions change. Add new durable data through the storage-process RPC boundary. Hydrate owners at application startup and keep serialization out of display components."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#add-a-suggestion-kind","title":"Add a suggestion kind","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Adding a kind affects the discriminated union and every exhaustive presentation or behavior decision. 1. Add the literal to SuggestionKind and a new union member in types.ts. 2. Decide whether it is text-insertable, stru","content":"Add a suggestion kind Adding a kind affects the discriminated union and every exhaustive presentation or behavior decision. 1. Add the literal to SuggestionKind and a new union member in types.ts. 2. Decide whether it is text-insertable, structural/reference-only, or requires a new action."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#add-a-custom-editor-block","title":"Add a custom editor block","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Register the block in writingSchema, then address all serialization boundaries: - accepted-document plain-text extraction; - external HTML behavior; - save/load schema compatibility; - focus and selection behavior; - age","content":"Add a custom editor block Register the block in writingSchema, then address all serialization boundaries: - accepted-document plain-text extraction; - external HTML behavior; - save/load schema compatibility; - focus and selection behavior; - agent-context inclusion or exclusion;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#implement-navigation-and-document-actions","title":"Implement navigation and document actions","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The following are static today: - New Document; - Library, Recent, Templates, Collections, Settings, Help, Archive; - Drafts, Review, Published; - history, export, share, and overflow actions. Before wiring buttons indiv","content":"Implement navigation and document actions The following are static today: - New Document; - Library, Recent, Templates, Collections, Settings, Help, Archive; - Drafts, Review, Published; - history, export, share, and overflow actions. Before wiring buttons individually, introduce the missing domain/state boundary:"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#extend-artifact-upload-or-source-retrieval","title":"Extend artifact upload or source retrieval","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The sidebar imports PDF, DOCX, Markdown, and text files through the main/storage boundary and shows persisted sources. That owner should distinguish: - upload state and errors; - stable artifact identity; - display metad","content":"Extend artifact upload or source retrieval The sidebar imports PDF, DOCX, Markdown, and text files through the main/storage boundary and shows persisted sources. That owner should distinguish: - upload state and errors; - stable artifact identity; - display metadata; - processing/indexing state;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#evolve-the-inbox-reducer-safely","title":"Evolve the inbox reducer safely","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Use a new reducer action for a new user intent. Avoid mutating arrays in components or exposing raw dispatch outside the hook. For every transition, consider: - live, pinned, and workspace copies; - selected detail; - ac","content":"Evolve the inbox reducer safely Use a new reducer action for a new user intent. Avoid mutating arrays in components or exposing raw dispatch outside the hook. For every transition, consider: - live, pinned, and workspace copies; - selected detail; - active preview; - viewed/unread counts;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#validate-external-suggestion-data","title":"Validate external suggestion data","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"TypeScript types do not validate network input. A production feed should parse runtime payloads before emitting them. Validation should cover: - known event and suggestion kinds; - non-empty identity/dedupe fields; - tim","content":"Validate external suggestion data TypeScript types do not validate network input. A production feed should parse runtime payloads before emitting them. Validation should cover: - known event and suggestion kinds; - non-empty identity/dedupe fields; - timestamps and source-label arrays;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#introduce-routing-or-server-rendering","title":"Introduce routing or server rendering","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The current code reads browser globals during state initialization and event handling. Server rendering would require guards or client-only boundaries for: - window.localStorage and window.matchMedia in App; - document q","content":"Introduce routing or server rendering The current code reads browser globals during state initialization and event handling. Server rendering would require guards or client-only boundaries for: - window.localStorage and window.matchMedia in App; - document queries and animation frames;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#performance-watch-points","title":"Performance watch points","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The current data volume is intentionally small. Revisit these choices as it grows: - suggestion deep copy uses JSON serialization; - workspace geometry commits update the whole reducer state; - large Mermaid diagrams ren","content":"Performance watch points The current data volume is intentionally small. Revisit these choices as it grows: - suggestion deep copy uses JSON serialization; - workspace geometry commits update the whole reducer state; - large Mermaid diagrams render client-side and inject full SVG;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#documentation-update-triggers","title":"Documentation update triggers","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Update this section when a change affects any of the following: - setup, Node support, scripts, or environment variables; - service or data contracts; - state ownership or persistence; - suggestion lifecycle invariants; ","content":"Documentation update triggers Update this section when a change affects any of the following: - setup, Node support, scripts, or environment variables; - service or data contracts; - state ownership or persistence; - suggestion lifecycle invariants; - editor schema and preview rules;"}];
